        <abstract> 
<p>Praise for ARW’s reply [<hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> 3 (1870): 49–50] to a paper by A. W. Bennett ["Natural selection from a mathematical point of view", <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> 3 (1870): 30–3] holding that mind is a leading cause of variation.</p>  
<p>Is reading proof of his "confounded book" [<hi rend="italic">Descent</hi>].</p> 
